Hi Ann.  I&#39;m a MAC user (OS 10.4.x).  I don&#39;t know if you use Audacity, but that program 
will change your audio output from 44100Hz to 96000Hz.  This will prevent sound from 
working on some sites.  For me, YouTube is a good example.  I have to reset my sound 
almost every time after using Audacity (I&#39;ve created a shortcut on my desktop to make it 
quick and easy).

I don&#39;t know if this will work for you, but try this path:  Applications &gt; Utilities &gt; Audio 
MIDI Setup (launch this application).  Then on the right side, under the words &quot;Audio 
Output&quot; there is a pulldown menu after the word FORMAT.  If it isn&#39;t 44100Hz, change it to 
this setting.   It took me forever and day to figure out what the problem was on my 
system.  Hope it works for you.  If this doesn&#39;t work, I&#39;m out of suggestions.   ;-)  Margaret

